As Muslim faithful in Nigeria celebrate Eid-el-Kabir tomorrow, Enugu State Governor, Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi, has urged them to continue to uphold and promote the core values of Islam for the sustenance of peace, unity and progress of the country. In a Sallah Message issued on Monday, Governor Ugwuanyi, who felicitated with President Muhammadu Buhari and other Muslim faithful, also wished them the guidance and blessings of Allah. He appealed to all Nigerians to continue to supplicate for the progress of the country through good deeds, sacrifice and abiding faith in God. Ugwuanyi said that “the ultimate goal remains our collective ability to live in peace and harmony, to cherish one another irrespective of religious, ethnic and political differences, for sustainable development of the nation.”